-# Intro - test =====================================================================
%p This document outlines whole range of common HTML elements and entities which can be used in page structure.
%p The main purpose of this document, is to provide code samples of HTML elements, as well as to help to build unified and precise design across all HTML system aspects.

%hr


-# Typography ================================================================
.styleguide-section
  %h3{ :class => 'styleguide-section--title', :id => 'styleguide-section-typography' } Typography
  %p.styleguide-section--description Typography - is very important part of every written piece of text. Its main role is to structure content in visual appealing way, to provide ability to read text comfortably, and understand the meaning of this information. Beside visual matter, typography is very important part of any HTML markup, which in its turn is necessary part of every Web document.
  =partial( 'styleguide/elements/typography' )

-# Lists =====================================================================
.styleguide-section
  %h3{ :class => 'styleguide-section--title', :id => 'styleguide-section-lists' } Lists
  %p.styleguide-section--description There are several list types you may use in markup, <abbr title="Unordered List">ul</abbr>, <abbr title="Ordered List">ol</abbr> and <abbr title="Definition List">dl</abbr>.
  =partial( 'styleguide/elements/lists' )

